parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pressure sensor can cause the engine to hesitate or stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle experiences reduced engine performance.

the vehicle experiences sudden speed drops.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Pump Electronics Module (PEM) Causing Intermittent Starting Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty PEM can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to unexpected stalling, loss of power, and difficulty restarting, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine cranks but does not turn over
fuel pump can be heard when key is turned in ignition
difficulty starting the vehicle
multiple attempts required to start the engine
fuel pressure builds slowly with each attempt
engine starts occasionally after repeated attempts
vehicle operates normally once started
difficulty restarting after 24-36 hours of inactivity.
